  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>portobello mushrooms</strong> to a tray and drizzle over the <strong>soy sauce</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until the mushrooms are cooked through and tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-creamy-mushroom-gnocchi/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the mushrooms are cooking, peel and roughly chop the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse the<strong> butterbeans</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>veg stock mix</strong> in 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-creamy-mushroom-gnocchi/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> the<strong> drained butterbeans</strong> and the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the garlic has softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-creamy-mushroom-gnocchi/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, transfer the <strong>butterbeans & garlic</strong> to a <strong>blender</strong>, reserving the pan</p><p>Add the<strong> veg stock</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> 'creamy' sauce</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-creamy-mushroom-gnocchi/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, tear the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> straight into the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p><p>Add the<strong> remaining butterbeans</strong> and the<strong> gnocchi</strong> and cook for a further 5-6 min or until everything is starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-creamy-mushroom-gnocchi/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> Chinese rice wine </strong>and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>'creamy' sauce</strong> and<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> and cook for a further 2-3 min or until the spinach has wilted and the sauce has thickened</p><p>Season to taste, adding more <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed – this is your <strong>'creamy' mushroom gnocchi</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-creamy-mushroom-gnocchi/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 7
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> 'creamy' mushroom gnocchi </strong>in bowls and top with a <strong>roasted portobello mushroom</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped chives </strong>and a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
